text: Lemhi County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 7,974 people lived there. The county seat and largest city is Salmon. == Communities == === Cities === * Leadore * Salmon === Unincorporated communities === * Carmen * Cobalt * Elk Bend * Gibbonsville * Lemhi * May * North Fork * Patterson * Shoup * Tendoy == References == Category:Idaho counties Category:1860s establishments in Idaho Territory Category:1869 establishments in the United States
